[http://www.flickr.com/photos/29079609@N02] @ Kilted Cowboy — well, for the year, it’s the Library of Congress to the rescue ;) with their <a href="http://memory.loc.gov/ammem/about/index.html" rel="nofollow"><i>American Memory Collection</i></a>.

This photo appeared in the <a href="http://memory.loc.gov/service/sgp/sgpnyt/1916/191602/19160213/0001.pdf" rel="nofollow">Picture Section</a> of <i>The New York Times</i> on February 13, 1916, with the following caption:<blockquote>”MISS CAMILLE BURGESS, Queen of the St. Paul Outdoor Sports Carnival, Entering the Ice Fort on Harriet Island Under an Arch of Ice Blocks. (<i>Photo by  Bain News Service</i>)”</blockquote>
